On Cuban Independence Day, the President extends his warmest wishes to the Cuban American community and the people of Cuba. He emphasizes the shared principles of self-governance, dignity, and freedom between Americans and Cubans. The President remembers patriots like José Martí, who fought for Cuba's independence and highlights the importance of a government that upholds democratic values, economic liberties, religious freedoms, and human rights. He also honors the contributions of Cuban Americans to the United States in various fields and expresses gratitude to those who serve in the military. The President and Melania send their best wishes to the people of Cuba and Cuban Americans in the United States.